    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- Chosen Palette: Energetic & Playful -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The infographic is designed with a top-down narrative flow. It starts with high-impact summary statistics ("big numbers") to give an immediate sense of the framework's scale. This is followed by a central doughnut chart that visualizes the distribution of capabilities across the main domains. The body of the page uses a responsive grid of cards, each dedicated to a primary domain, allowing users to explore the details. This structure guides the user from a broad overview to specific details, making the complex hierarchy easy to understand. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Key Metrics (Domains, Areas, etc.): Goal: Inform. Method: Large, bold text. Justification: These "big number" callouts act as an effective hook, quickly conveying the scope and scale of the data. NO SVG is used.
        - Domain Distribution: Goal: Compare Composition. Viz: Doughnut Chart (Chart.js/Canvas). Justification: This is ideal for showing parts of a whole, clearly illustrating the relative size of each primary domain. It serves as a visual centerpiece. Tooltip and label wrapping are included for clarity. NO SVG is used.
        - Hierarchical Breakdown: Goal: Organize. Method: Styled HTML cards with nested lists (Tailwind). Justification: For this type of nested textual data, a clean card layout with lists is far more readable and scannable than a complex diagram, especially on various screen sizes. Unicode characters are used for notes. NO SVG/Mermaid is used. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
